author: The Record
title: H.S. football: Glen Rock under the lights - Football
text:
The Glen Rock football team will play its first home game under the lights tonight at Alan Deaett Field. 
The Panthers enter the 6 p.m. NJIC Liberty Division game against New Milford with a 3-1 record. They're coming off consecutive wins over Hawthorne (41-18), Pompton Lakes (22-19) and Waldwick/Midland Park (34-19) after an opening-day loss to Rutherford (26-22). 
New Milford (2-2, 1-1) fell to Hawthorne, 29-7, last week.
